			<common:generalComment xml:lang="en">Vat dyeing is a process that refers to dyeing that takes place in a bucket or vat. The original vat dye is indigo, often produced synthetically. Vat dyes are water-insoluble dyes used particularly on cellulosic fibres. The dye is applied in a soluble, reduced form to impregnate the fibre and then oxidized back to its original insoluble form. Vat dyes are fast to light and washing and can produce brilliant colours in most shades. Despite their higher cost, vat dyes have been gaining popularity.</common:generalComment>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="zh">大桶染色是指在桶中进行染色的工艺。最初的大桶染料是靛蓝，通常是人工合成的。大桶染料是不溶于水的染料，尤其用于纤维素纤维。染料以可溶、还原的形式应用于浸渍纤维，然后氧化回原来的不溶形式。大桶染料的耐光性和耐洗性都很好，能染成大多数色调的艳丽色彩。尽管大桶染料的成本较高，但却越来越受欢迎。</common:generalComment>
